EigenLayer - The Point to the Points
Kunal Goel

Jan 30, 2024 ⋅  9 min read

Key Insights

  • EigenLayer is perhaps the most highly anticipated launch of 2024. With the opportunity it presents and a points-based incentive program, it has lured ETH capital worth $1.8 billion.
  • While points have been untradable, with some DeFi trickery, users have managed to strip the airdrop value from their restaked ETH. This airdrop value represents a very significant fixed APY of 30%.
  • However, a greater opportunity may be available to those willing to sell this high APY to efficiently farm the EigenLayer airdrop.

EigenLayer is one of the most exciting upcoming launches for 2024. It is a restaking primitive that allows ETH validators to secure protocols beyond just the Ethereum blockchain. The protocols that utilize EigenLayer and ETH's security are called Actively Validated Services or AVS. Some planned AVSs are data availability layers, decentralized sequencers, oracles, and bridges.

EigenLayer promises to be a win-win-win for its ecosystem participants.

  • AVSs can quickly bootstrap significant economic security from a large pool of validators at a lower cost than if they set up their own chain.
  • ETH stakers unlock greater capital efficiency and can earn additional yield by opting in to secure AVSs.
  • And finally, ETH becomes a general-purpose security asset, allowing it to meet greater security demand unbounded by the capabilities of its execution and consensus layers.

As such, Ethereum users are excited about the opportunity that EigenLayer represents. Since its mainnet launch in June 2023, EigenLayer has amassed deposits of 800,000+ ETH and liquid staking tokens (LSTs) worth more than $1.8 billion. Since AVSs are not live yet, the only incentives to lock up ETH in EigenLayer are its restaking points. While the point of the points is not explicitly known, it is expected that they represent a proportional share in a future EigenLayer token airdrop, similar to other points-based incentive programs in crypto like Blur, friend.tech, and Rainbow Wallet.

Points-based incentives are an improvement over retroactive airdrops as they reward long-term consistent usage over short-term mercenary farming. In a points-based incentive system, protocols award points to users engaging in productive activities and track them privately in their databases. As such, users cannot trade these points on the blockchain. However, through the magic of DeFi composability, users can now trade EigenLayer points using the interest rate derivatives platform Pendle.

The Pendulum Swings

Pendle is an interest rates derivatives platform that allows users to separate the principal and yield from yield-bearing assets like stETH and sDAI. It converts a yield-bearing asset into two individually tradable tokens – a Principal Token (PT) and a Yield Token (YT). The PT functions like a zero-coupon bond, redeemable for the original asset on maturity. The YT entitles the holder to receive the future yield of the asset up to the maturity date.

So far, Pendle’s product offering of yield-bearing LSTs and USD-stablecoins has had limited speculatory use as the yields are relatively stable. However, with the recent launch of liquid restaking token-based pools, Pendle has unlocked speculation on EigenLayer points.

Liquid Restaking <> Pendle

Liquid restaking protocols like ether.fi and Kelp DAO deposit ETH into EigenLayer on behalf of their users and issue liquid restaking tokens (LRTs) in return. As the LRT protocols deposit ETH into EigenLayer, they earn EigenLayer restaking points, not the users. However, there is an understanding that protocols will distribute any airdrops to LRT holders. Recently, through a partnership with Pendle, LRT protocols have integrated Pendle assets. Now, when a user deposits an LRT into a Pendle contract, the LRT protocol tracks this to distribute any future points to the holder of the YT instead. In effect, users can now strip the potential airdrop component of EigenLayer points from the LRT into the YT. And they buy or sell their potential EigenLayer airdrops by trading the YT.

The two popular Pendle LRT integrations have been with ether.fi and KelpDAO. Their respective YTs for June 2024 expiries are priced at ~$240 by the market, implying an APY of ~30%. This restaking APY is much higher than the basic ETH staking rewards of 3-4%.

A Game of Points

The LRT integration with Pendle has been widely successful. In just 18 days since launch, Pendle has amassed a TVL of $200 million in liquid restaking tokens, which now contribute to 40% of its total TVL. Users on both sides of the YT trade find the opportunity promising: a fixed 30% APY for the risk-averse and capital-efficient points for the EigenLayer hopefuls.

Pricing the Points

With publicly available information, we can estimate the price paid per point at the current values for Pendle LRT pools.

  • Yield tokens for eETH (ether.fi restaked ETH) and rsETH (Kelp DAO restaked ETH) are trading at ~$240 for June 27, 2024 expiries.
  • With ~$30 in expected ETH staking rewards, the speculatory value for restaked points is $210.
  • There are 154 days remaining for expiry, and with the earnings rate of 1 point per hour per ETH, YT holders can expect to earn 3,696 points till expiry.
  • Therefore, YT buyers are paying $0.06 per restaked point if they hold till maturity.

Valuing the Points

The value per point requires a few assumptions.

  • EigenLayer airdrop value is a function of the market cap for EigenLayer and the allocation airdropped. If EigenLayer airdrops 10% of its token supply and is priced between Lido ($3 billion) and Celestia ($18 billion), the value of the airdrop may range between $300 million and $1.5 billion. While this may seem high, there is precedent with the ARB airdrop, where users received 11.62% supply, worth $1.6 billion on launch day.
  • The airdrop date is unknowable, but the expected date for mainnet launch is Q1-Q2 2024, per an interview by the EigenLayer founder, Sreeram Kannan.
    • The airdrop date impacts two inputs. It affects the total points earned by all restakers and a later airdrop increases the base, reducing the value per point. Second, it is unclear whether points earned after airdrop will have any value. Therefore, we conservatively assume that YT holders earn points until maturity or airdrop date, whichever is earlier.
  • ETH deposited in EigenLayer affects the total points distributed. Currently, 820,000 ETH is deposited. We can expect this to grow as EigenLayer removes deposit caps on LSTs. In our base case, we assume 3 million ETH will be deposited into EigenLayer by June 30, 2024. This calculation assumes monthly deposits of 440,000 ETH, comparable to December deposits of 400,000 ETH when LST restaking was last available.
  • Using the reward rate of 1 point per hour per ETH and linear growth in ETH restaked, we calculate the total restaking points on the airdrop date.
  • Finally, we can estimate the value per point by dividing the airdrop value by the total restaking points. By comparing the value to the price paid per point from the calculation in the previous section, we can estimate the potential payoff for holding the Pendle YT token.
  • Our base case estimates a ~100% upside from the current price of $0.06 per point.

This result makes intuitive sense as well. Restaking points are being sold cheaply by risk-averse participants because 30% fixed APY on ETH is much higher than standard market conditions. The risk-taking buyers are probably fewer in number and are pricing the market in their favor.

Further, our calculation only considers the value of the EigenLayer airdrop. The LRT protocols involved, ether.fi and Kelp DAO have their own points program, and any airdrops from them or other ecosystem players will further increase the payoff for YT holders.

Point Payoff Matrix

A sensitivity analysis of different airdrop values and dates on the potential payoffs has been shown above by comparing the value calculated per point to the cost of $0.06. The analysis assumes that 3 million ETH is deposited into EigenLayer, irrespective of the airdrop date.

A larger airdrop is naturally beneficial for YT holders. However, the matrix shows that the best case for YT holders is that the airdrop is conducted near their maturity date on June 27, 2024. This makes sense as an early airdrop means that YT holders’ leveraged point farming is less effective. And a later airdrop has a worse payoff, as YT holders do not earn points after maturity.

The no profit, no loss scenario would be a late Q2 airdrop valued at ~$500 million. This valuation would be at the lower end of market expectations, much closer to Lido than Celestia. An airdrop value above $1 billion would be profitable irrespective of the airdrop date, assuming 3 million ETH are restaked on EigenLayer.

Pointing out the Risks

While there is a promising opportunity, there are risks outside EigenLayer's airdrop value and date.

Enhanced Smart Contract Risk

While smart contract risk is pervasive in any application, Pendle's LRT pools are exposed to at least three protocols' smart contracts – EigenLayer, the restaking protocol, and Pendle itself. In the case of LST restaking for KelpDAO, funds are also exposed to the smart contracts of the liquid staking protocol.

Missing Airdrops

Pendle YT holders may miss out on airdrops by other protocols that reward EigenLayer restakers. As a recent example, Alt Layer did not airdrop to Pendle YT holders even though direct EigenLayer stakers and LRT holders qualified.

Capped Airdrops

EigenLayer and other airdrops may not distribute the tokens per point but rather bucket them or cap the highest points earned per address. This would mean larger addresses like those of LRT protocols may earn a smaller airdrop per point.

The Final Point

EigenLayer is among the highly anticipated launches of 2024. With the opportunity it presents and a points-based incentive program, it has lured ETH capital worth $1.8 billion. While points have been untradable, with some DeFi trickery, users can now strip the airdrop value from their restaked ETH. This airdrop value represents a very significant fixed APY of 30%. But the opportunity may be even higher for the brave souls willing to sell this high APY for leveraged airdrop farming.
